        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} in the sun, read, snorkeled, and enjoyed the late summer feeling to the fullest. This time the water was particularly clear - and even a small school of barracudas showed up. A nice end to our time on the island. </p>
        <p> On the last evening, we strolled to the Plaza del Duque Mall after dinner. Like the Siam Mall, not quite our thing - but the walk along the promenade was worth it. Light breeze, the lights, a bit of ocean sound in the background... the perfect last evening moment. </p>
        <p> The last morning it was time to slowly say goodbye. While Basti was already checking out, I spontaneously treated myself to an appointment at the nail salon. My nails were finally long and stable enough to make it worthwhile - and that's how Basti's Christmas present from 2020 was redeemed. Some things just need time. </p>
        <p> Our transfer bus was ready on time at 12:30 p.m. We had to wait at the airport because the check-in counter wasn't open yet - but with the sun at our backs, we could wait quite comfortably. The plane was almost empty, just 94 people on board. Pure luxury: endless space. </p>

